1.name: Place of terms of delivery
1.desc:
(3018) Point or port of departure, shipment or destination, as
                                    required under the applicable terms of delivery, e.g. Incoterms.

2.name: Payment place
2.desc:
Place where funds are to be, or have been made available to the
                                    creditor.

3.name: Tare check place
3.desc:
Place where equipment tare has been or must be checked for official
                                    assessment.

4.name: Goods receipt place
4.desc: Place at which the goods have been received.

5.name: Place of departure
5.desc:
(3214) Port, airport or other location from which a means of transport
                                    or transport equipment is scheduled to depart or has departed.

7.name: Place of delivery
7.desc:
(3246) Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered under
                                    transport contract terms (operational term).

8.name: Place of destination
8.desc:
Port, airport or other location to which a means of transport or
                                    transport equipment is destined.

9.name: Place/port of loading
9.desc:
(3334 + 3230) Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or
                                    other place at which the goods (cargo) are loaded on to the means of transport being
                                    used for their carriage.

10.name: Place of acceptance
10.desc: (3348) Place at which the goods are taken over by the carrier.

11.name: Place/port of discharge
11.desc:
(3392 + 3414) Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or
                                    other place at which the goods (cargo) are unloaded from the means of transport
                                    having been used for their carriage.

12.name: Port of discharge
12.desc:
Port at which the goods are discharged from the vessel used for their
                                    transport.

13.name: Place of transhipment
13.desc:
(3424) Place where goods are transferred from one means of transport
                                    to another (operational term).

14.name: Location of goods
14.desc:
(3384) Place where goods are located and where they are available for
                                    examination.

15.name: Place of transfer responsibility
15.desc: Place where the responsibility is transferred.

16.name: Place of transfer of ownership
16.desc: Place where the ownership of the goods is transferred.

17.name: Border crossing place
17.desc: Place where goods are transported across a country border.

18.name: Warehouse
18.desc: (3156) Warehouse where a particular consignment has been stored.

19.name: Factory/plant
19.desc: Factory/plant relevant for a particular consignment.

20.name: Place of ultimate destination of goods
20.desc: Place where goods will ultimately be delivered.

21.name: Terms of sale place
21.desc:
Place of departure, shipment or destination as specified in the terms
                                    of sale agreed between the parties.

22.name: Customs office of clearance
22.desc: (3080) Place where Customs clearance procedure occur (CCC).

23.name: Port of release
23.desc: Port where goods are released from Customs custody.

24.name: Port of entry
24.desc: Port where final documentation is filed for Customs Entry processing.

25.name: Country
25.desc: Country relevant for a particular transaction.

26.name: City
26.desc: City or town relevant for a particular transaction or consignment.

27.name: Country of origin
27.desc:
[3238] Country in which the goods have been produced or manufactured,
                                    according to criteria laid down for the purposes of application of the Customs
                                    tariff, of quantitative restrictions, or of any other measure related to trade.

28.name: Country of destination of goods
28.desc: Country to which the goods are to be delivered.

29.name: Railway station
29.desc:
Name or identification of a railway station/yard relevant to a
                                    particular consignment.

30.name: Country of source
30.desc:
Country in which raw material or components were originally produced
                                    prior to manufacture or assembly in another country.

31.name: Building
31.desc:
A building or part thereof relevant to a particular consignment or
                                    transaction.

32.name: Beginning of chargeable section
32.desc:
First rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A
                                    complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are
                                    separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

33.name: Baseport of discharge
33.desc:
The port of discharge according to the tariff as opposed to the
                                    operational port of discharge. The goods may or may not be actually discharged at
                                    that port on the main transport.

34.name: Baseport of loading
34.desc:
The port of loading according to the tariff as opposed to the
                                    operational port of loading. The goods may or may not be actually loaded at that
                                    port on the main transport.

35.name: Country of exportation/despatch
35.desc:
(3220) Country from which the goods were initially exported to the
                                    importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate
                                    countries. Syn.: country whence consigned. Country of despatch: country from which
                                    goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

36.name: Country of ultimate destination
36.desc:
(3216) Country known to the consignor or his agent at the time of
                                    despatch to be the final country to which the goods are to be delivered.

37.name: Country of last consignment
37.desc:
[3331] Country where the goods are loaded onto the means of transport
                                    used for their importation.

38.name: Country of first destination
38.desc:
[3219] Country where the goods are offloaded from the means of
                                    transport used for their exportation.

39.name: Country of production
39.desc: Country where item has been or will be produced.

40.name: Country of trading
40.desc: Country where item has been or will be traded.

41.name: Customs office of entry
41.desc:
[3088] Customs office at which the goods enter the country of
                                    destination.

42.name: Customs office of exit
42.desc:
[3096] Customs office at which the goods leave the country of
                                    dispatch/export.

43.name: Place of Customs examination
43.desc:
Place where Customs undertakes a physical inspection of goods to
                                    satisfy themselves that the goods' nature, origin, condition, quantity and value are
                                    in accordance with the particulars furnished on the goods declaration (CCC).

44.name: Place of authentication of document
44.desc:
(3410) Place where document is signed or otherwise authenticated.
                                    Synonym: Place of issue of document.

45.name: Customs office of destination (transit)
45.desc:
(3086) Customs office at which a transit operation is terminated.
                                    Synonym: Customs office of transit termination.

46.name: Region of despatch
46.desc:
Region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs
                                    union.

47.name: Region of destination
47.desc:
Region known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to
                                    be the final region to which the goods are to be delivered.

48.name: Region of production
48.desc: Region where item has been or will be produced.

50.name: Customs office of transit
50.desc:
[3106] Customs office which is competent for transit formalities en
                                    route.

51.name: Country of invalid transit guarantee
51.desc:
Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods
                                    under a transit procedure is not valid.

52.name: Country of destination (transit)
52.desc:
Country at which a Customs transit operation is terminated. Synonym:
                                    Country of transit termination.

53.name: Charge and freight due from
53.desc: Place or point from which charges and freight are charged.

54.name: Manufacturing department
54.desc:
A department within the manufacturing area (e.g. lacquering,
                                    assembly).

55.name: Charges and freight payable to
55.desc:
[3274] Name of place up to which freight charges and other charges are
                                    to be paid.

56.name: End of chargeable section
56.desc:
Last rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A
                                    complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are
                                    separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

57.name: Place of payment
57.desc:
Name of the location at which freight and charges for main transport
                                    are payable.

58.name: Full track loading or unloading
58.desc:
Identification of the station proceeding to the loading or unloading
                                    of a rail wagon on a full track site. (Used only when a rail station is obliged to
                                    transfer the load on another wagon for technical reasons - e.g. damage).

59.name: Place of loss
59.desc: To identify the location where the loss occurred.

60.name: Place of arrival
60.desc: Place at which the transport means arrives.

61.name: Next port of call
61.desc: Next port which the vessel is going to call upon.

62.name: On-carriage port
62.desc:
Port of discharge at which the cargo is discharged from the vessel,
                                    used for transport after the main transport (transit port).

63.name: Sub-project location
63.desc: A place at which works occur referring to a sub-project.

64.name: First optional place of discharge
64.desc:
The first optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the
                                    transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

65.name: Final port or place of discharge
65.desc:
Name of the seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other
                                    place at which the goods (cargo) are finally (to be) unloaded from the means of
                                    transport used for their carriage according to the transport contract.

66.name: Express railway station
66.desc: Railway station offering express transportation services.

67.name: Mixed cargo railway station
67.desc: Railway station offering mixed cargo transportation services .

68.name: Second optional place of discharge
68.desc:
The second optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the
                                    transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of shipper.

69.name: Next non-discharge port of call
69.desc:
A code to identify the next port of call for a vessel where no cargo
                                    will be discharged.

70.name: Third optional place of discharge
70.desc:
The third optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the
                                    transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

71.name: Reconsolidation point
71.desc: A place where cargo is reconsolidated.

72.name: Fourth optional place of discharge
72.desc:
The fourth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the
                                    transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

73.name: Bill of lading release office
73.desc: A location where bills of lading are released to customers.

74.name: Transhipment excluding this place
74.desc:
Place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to
                                    another means of transport is not authorised.

75.name: Transhipment limited to this place
75.desc:
Only place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to
                                    another means of transport is authorised.

76.name: Original port of loading
76.desc: The port where the goods were first loaded on a vessel.

77.name: First port of call - non-discharging
77.desc:
Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially
                                    arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will
                                    not be discharging cargoes.

78.name: First port of call - discharging
78.desc:
Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially
                                    arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will
                                    be discharging cargoes.

79.name: Place/port of first entry
79.desc:
Place or port where final documentation is filed for Customs entry
                                    processing.

80.name: Place of despatch
80.desc:
Place at which the goods are taken over for carriage (operational
                                    term), if different from the transport contract place of acceptance (see: 10).
                                    Synonym: Place of origin of carriage.

81.name: Fifth optional place of discharge
81.desc:
The fifth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the
                                    transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

82.name: Pre-carriage port
82.desc:
Port of loading at which the cargo is loaded on the pre- carriage
                                    vessel used for the transport prior to the main transport.

83.name: Place of delivery (by on carriage)
83.desc: Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered.

84.name: Transport contract place of acceptance
84.desc:
Place at which the goods are taken over by the carrier according to
                                    the contract of carriage.

85.name: Transport contract place of destination
85.desc: Place to which the goods are destined.

86.name: Country of valid transit guarantee
86.desc:
Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods
                                    under a transit procedure is valid.

87.name: Place/port of conveyance initial arrival
87.desc:
Place/port in the country of destination where the conveyance
                                    initially arrives from the 'Last place/port of call of conveyance' (125).

88.name: Place of receipt
88.desc:
Identification of the location at which the cargo is actually
                                    received.

90.name: Special treatment place
90.desc:
Place where one or more special treatments have happened or must
                                    happen.

91.name: Place of document issue
91.desc: The place or location where a document is issued.

93.name: Station of application of additional costs
93.desc:
Rail station where, according to the transport contract, some
                                    chargeable operations must happen (re-weighting, re-fixing of the load, control on
                                    equipment and on consignment, etc.).

94.name: Previous port of call
94.desc: Previous port which the vessel has called upon.

95.name: Sailing destination area
95.desc: Geographical area to which the vessel's trip is destined.

96.name: Place of lodgement of documents
96.desc:
Customs station where, required documents for Customs declarations,
                                    have been lodged.

97.name: Optional place of discharge
97.desc:
The optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the bill of
                                    lading where cargo is discharged at the option of the shipper.

98.name: Place of empty equipment despatch
98.desc: The location from which empty equipment is despatched.

99.name: Place of empty equipment return
99.desc: The location to which empty equipment is returned.

100.name: Place/port of warehouse entry
100.desc:
Location (e.g. district) within a Customs territory where a warehouse
                                    entry was filed to enter merchandise into a Customs bonded warehouse.

101.name: Country of first sale
101.desc: Name of country where firstly a sale took place.

102.name: Country of purchase
102.desc:
[3394] Country where the importer's co-contractor is domiciled or has
                                    his business.

103.name: Place of transfer
103.desc:
Place at which goods are transferred from one carrier to another
                                    (contractual term).

104.name: Place of deconsolidation
104.desc:
Place where a large consignment is de-grouped into smaller
                                    consignments.

105.name: Place of consumption
105.desc:
Place/location where goods enter the marketplace (commerce) of the
                                    importing country.

106.name: Region of origin
106.desc:
Region in which the goods have been produced or manufactured according
                                    to the criteria laid down for the purposes of the application of the Customs tariff,
                                    of quantitative restrictions or of any other measures related to trade (see: 3238).

107.name: Place of consolidation
107.desc:
Place where smaller consignments of goods are grouped together into a
                                    large consignment to be transported as a larger unit.

108.name: Rate combination point
108.desc: Point over which sector rates are combined.

109.name: Place of prolongation decision of delivery delay
109.desc: Place where it has been decided to prolong the delivery delay.

110.name: Recharging place/location
110.desc:
Place/location where a consignment has been changed of destination and
                                    is subject to a recharge note. (Complementary orders to modify the routing of the
                                    transport may be given, upon which a new charge calculation may be applied by the
                                    carrier).

111.name: Customs office of despatch
111.desc:
Customs office from which goods are despatched between countries of a
                                    Customs union.

112.name: Region of equipment availability
112.desc:
Region in which a piece of equipment is requested to be made available
                                    for on-hire.

113.name: Country of despatch
113.desc: Country from which goods are despatched within a Customs union.

114.name: Customs office of export
114.desc:
Customs office from which goods are taken out of the Customs territory
                                    (CCC).

115.name: Free zone of export
115.desc:
Foreign free zone (desc: see 1131 = 131) from which goods are exported
                                    to the country of importation.

116.name: Region of export/despatch
116.desc:
Region from which the goods were initially exported to the importing
                                    country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries.
                                    Region of despatch: region from which goods are despatched between countries of a
                                    Customs union.

117.name: Place of collection
117.desc: Place where goods are to be or could be picked up (collected).

118.name: Customs office of departure
118.desc: Customs office at which a Customs transit operation commences (CCC).

119.name: Customs office of transit guarantee
119.desc:
[3110] Customs office at which a security or guarantee for the
                                    movement of goods under a transit procedure is lodged.

120.name: Country of transhipment
120.desc:
Country where goods are transferred under Customs control from the
                                    importing means of transport to the exporting means of transport within the area of
                                    one Customs office which is the office of both importation and exportation (CCC).

121.name: Country of sale
121.desc:
[3116] Country where exporter's co-contractor is domiciled or has his
                                    business.

122.name: Customs office of destination
122.desc: Customs office where the goods are to be cleared (CCC).

123.name: Wagon-load railway station
123.desc: A railway station where rail wagons are loaded.

124.name: Siding
124.desc:
A short railway track for loading or unloading rail wagons, or
                                    bypassing of trains, connected with a main track by switch.

125.name: Last place/port of call of conveyance
125.desc:
Conveyance departed from this last foreign place/port of call to go to
                                    'Place/port of conveyance initial arrival' (87).

126.name: Country of previous Customs procedure
126.desc:
Country in which the Customs declaration for the previous Customs
                                    procedure has been lodged.

127.name: Customs office of registration of previous Customs declaration
127.desc: Customs office where the previous Customs declaration has been lodged.

128.name: Participant sender location
128.desc:
Place where a participant in the movement of goods is located and can
                                    be contacted.

129.name: Wage negotiation district
129.desc:
The district to which workers belong for the purposes of union wage
                                    negotiation.

130.name: Place of ultimate destination of conveyance
130.desc:
Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place to
                                    which a means of transport is ultimately destined.

131.name: Place of loading of empty equipment
131.desc:
Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where
                                    empty equipment (e.g. containers) was loaded onto means of transport.

132.name: Place of discharge of empty equipment
132.desc:
Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where
                                    empty equipment (e.g. containers) was unloaded from means of transport.

133.name: Region of delivery
133.desc:
(3246) Region to which the goods are to be finally delivered under
                                    transport contract terms (operational term).

134.name: Petroleum warehouse
134.desc: Bonded petroleum warehouse or the supplier source.

135.name: Place of entry (Customs)
135.desc: Place at which the goods enter the Customs territory.

136.name: Living animals care place
136.desc: Place where living animal cares are provided.

137.name: Re-icing place
137.desc: Place where re-icing must be executed.

138.name: Weighting place
138.desc: Place where weight can be ascertained.

139.name: Marshalling yard
139.desc:
Station where the wagons are disconnected and reconnected to form a
                                    new train.

140.name: Stopping station
140.desc:
Station where the train must stop or is stopped for unexpected
                                    handling.

141.name: Loading dock
141.desc: Platform specially equipped for loading and unloading of rail wagons.

142.name: Port connection
142.desc: Track connecting a rail station to a dock.

143.name: Place of expiry
143.desc:
Place where the documentary credit expires for presentation of
                                    required documents.

144.name: Place of negotiation
144.desc: Place where the documentary credit is to be presented for negotiation.

145.name: Claims payable place
145.desc: Place where insurance claims are payable.

146.name: Documentary credit available in
146.desc: Place where the documentary credit is available with any bank.

147.name: Stowage cell
147.desc: Location on a vessel where units can be stowed.

148.name: For transportation to
148.desc: Place/country where goods are to be transported to.

149.name: Loading on board/despatch/taking in charge at/from
149.desc:
Place/country where goods have to be loaded on board, despatched or
                                    taken in charge.

150.name: Container stack position
150.desc: Stack position of a container at a terminal, depot or freight station.

151.name: Private box
151.desc:
A private box used for pick-up and delivery of packages, e.g. of
                                    express packages.

152.name: Next port of discharge
152.desc:
Next port at which goods are discharged from the vessel used for their
                                    transport.

153.name: Port of call
153.desc: Port where a vessel has called upon or will call upon.

154.name: Place/location of on-hire
154.desc: Place/location where an object is contracted for use.

155.name: Place/location of off-hire
155.desc: Place/location where an object's contract for use ends.

156.name: Other carriers terminal
156.desc:
A carrier terminal belonging to a carrier other than the original
                                    carrier.

157.name: Country of Value Added Tax (VAT) jurisdiction
157.desc:
The country governing the VAT regulation to which the transaction is
                                    subject.

158.name: Contact location
158.desc: The site where a contact is located.

159.name: Additional internal destination
159.desc:
Any location within the consignee's premises where the goods are moved
                                    to.

160.name: Foreign port of call
160.desc:
A code to identify the foreign port where the vessel calls at or will
                                    call at.

161.name: Maintenance location
161.desc: A location where maintenance has been or will be performed.

162.name: Place or location of sale
162.desc: Place or location at which the sale takes place.

163.name: Direct investment country
163.desc: Country in which a direct investment is made or withdrawn.

164.name: Berth
164.desc: Place or location in a port where a vessel is moored.

165.name: Construction country
165.desc: Country in which the construction work is made.

166.name: Donation acting country
166.desc: Country acting in the donation of aid.

167.name: Payment transaction country
167.desc: Country of the foreign counterpart of the payment transaction.

168.name: Physical place of return of item
168.desc:
Physical place at which the item is returned, i.e. the location where
                                    the supplier receives the item form the customer.

169.name: Relay port
169.desc:
A location where cargo is transferred from one means of transport to
                                    another means of transport owned or operated by the same carrier under the same bill
                                    of lading.

170.name: Final port of discharge
170.desc:
Last port at which cargo is unloaded from a vessel before the cargo is
                                    moved to a place of delivery or destination.

171.name: Place of destination for pre-stacking prior to stowage
171.desc:
The destination location for which items are to be pre- stacked prior
                                    to being stowed together on a means of transport.

172.name: Reporting location
172.desc: The location to which the information being reported is applicable.

173.name: Transport contract place of despatch
173.desc: A place from which goods are despatched as per transport contract.

174.name: Place of residence
174.desc: A place where a party lives.

175.name: Activity location
175.desc: A place at which the activity occurs.

177.name: Construction site
177.desc: A place at which construction works occur.

178.name: Port of embarkation
178.desc: Port where the person embarks onto the conveyance.

179.name: Port of disembarkation
179.desc: Port where the person disembarks from the conveyance.

180.name: Place of birth
180.desc: Place where the person was born.

181.name: Registered office
181.desc: Identifies the place or location of a registered office.

183.name: Place of business
183.desc: Identifies the place or location of a business.

185.name: Location to send mail
185.desc: Identifies the location to which mail is sent.

186.name: Foreign registration location
186.desc: Identifies the place or location of foreign registration.

187.name: Tax filed from location
187.desc: Identifies the location from which taxes are filed.

188.name: Filing location
188.desc: Identifies the location of the filing entity.

189.name: Former location
189.desc: Identifies an earlier or previous place or location.

190.name: Head office
190.desc: Identifies the place or location of a head office.

191.name: Property
191.desc: Identifies the place or location of property.

192.name: Correct location
192.desc: Identifies the correct place or location.

193.name: Branch location
193.desc: Identifies the place or location of a branch.

194.name: Former registered location
194.desc: Identifies the former registered location of an entity.

195.name: Future location
195.desc: Location to be used in the future.

197.name: Place of inquiry
197.desc: Place to which an inquiry is made.

199.name: Country of last source
199.desc: The country where a product or service was last sourced.

200.name: Place of handling
200.desc: Place where a handling operation is to be, or has been, performed.

201.name: Country of origin as defined by transportation agency
201.desc: Country of origin as defined by the transportation agency.

203.name: Sample location
203.desc: Code identifying the location from which a sample is taken.

204.name: Hospital Advanced Dependency Unit (ADU)
204.desc: A designated unit in a hospital for advanced dependency nursing care.

205.name: Hospital Neonatal Intensive Care Unit (NICU)
205.desc:
A designated unit in a hospital for the provision of intensive care to
                                    neonates.

206.name: Hospital Paediatric Care Unit (PCU)
206.desc:
A designated unit in a hospital for the provision of care to
                                    paediatric patients.

207.name: Hospital Intensive Care Unit (ICU)
207.desc: An intensive care unit in a hospital.

208.name: Hospital luxury room
208.desc: A room in a hospital for patient accommodation of superior standard.

209.name: Hospital shared room
209.desc: A room in a hospital for shared accommodation of patients.

210.name: Hospital private room
210.desc: A room in a hospital for private accommodation of a patient.

211.name: Bidding area
211.desc:
An area for which bids can be made with the same price applicable to
                                    the whole area.

212.name: Price area
212.desc: An area for which the same price is applicable to the whole area.

213.name: Country of destination of equipment
213.desc: Country of the last place where the equipment will stop.

214.name: Aircraft airport stand
214.desc: Code used to specify the airport stand allocated to the aircraft.

215.name: Airport passenger terminal
215.desc:
Code used to specify the airport terminal used for the embarking or
                                    disembarking of passengers.

216.name: Previous berth
216.desc: Place or location in a port where a vessel was previously moored.

217.name: Next berth
217.desc:
Place or location in a port where a vessel will be moored, after
                                    moving from the current location.

218.name: Entity location
218.desc: Identifies the place or location of the entity.

219.name: Goods depot
219.desc: Depot where goods are received and are available for pick-up.

220.name: Disinfecting place
220.desc: Place where disinfection has been or must be performed.

222.name: Place of live animal care
222.desc: Place where live animal care has been or must be provided.

223.name: Phytosanitary control place
223.desc: Place where phytosanitary control has been or must be performed.

224.name: Place for re-icing or de-icing
224.desc: Place where re-icing or de-icing has been or must be performed.

225.name: Place of refuelling
225.desc: Place where refuelling has been or must be performed.

226.name: Place of provision of an unexpected service
226.desc: Place where an unexpected service has been or must be provided.

227.name: Private container terminal
227.desc: Container terminal managed or owned by a private company.

228.name: Railway container terminal
228.desc: Container terminal managed or owned by a railway company.

229.name: Inspection site
229.desc: The site where an inspection takes or took place.

230.name: Request only stop
230.desc: A location where a stop is only made on request.

232.name: Source power area
232.desc: The area that is the source of power.

233.name: Sink power area
233.desc: The area that is the destination of power.

234.name: Scheduled berth
234.desc: Place or location in a port where a vessel is scheduled to be moored.

235.name: Scheduled berth, bow
235.desc:
